Olivia Newton-John died at the age of 73 in August following a decades-long battle with cancer. Six months on a memorial service has been held for the Grease legend, with many Hollywood stars paying tribute to the late actress. Her daughter, Chloe Lattanzi, was supported by her husband as she took to the stage to remember her late mother, admitting she feels like a "little girl" without her. Olivia's husband Josh Easterling also took to the stage to remember his "magical" late wife, as he tries to "carry Olivia's presence" with him. Hollywood stars including Nicole Kidman, Elton John, Dolly Parton and Mariah Carey were among those who appeared via video link to remember the actress.